article.headline: Penn St. 80, Robert Morris 61
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. -- Tim Frazier scored 19 points to lead Penn State to an 80-61 victory over Robert Morris on Monday night. Chris Babb added 15 points and Jeff Brooks had 12 points and five rebounds for the Nittany Lions (2-0), who are on a seven-game winning streak dating back to last season. Russell Johnson scored 11 points and had five rebounds to lead Robert Morris (0-2). Rob Robinson had nine of the Colonials' 31 rebounds and added eight points. The Nittany Lions' success on 3-pointers highlighted the team's offense. Penn State shot 12-for-26 from outside the circle, with Babb going 5-for-9 from 3-point range. Penn State had the slight edge at the break, leading Robert Morris 34-33. The Nittany Lions pulled away quickly in the second half, sparked by a dunk by Talor Battle off a steal with just over 17 minutes left to put the Nittany Lions up 47-35.
